<chapter>
  <title>Uses On Screen Display to show personal print quota information with pykosd</title>
  <para>Last modified on $Date$</para>
  
  <para>
    <filename>pykosd</filename> is a graphical <application>X Window</application> application which when launched 
    will display print quota information for the current user.
  </para>  
  
  <para>
    Whenever you launch <filename>pykosd</filename>, it will display the current user's print quota
    information in the top-left corner of the screen, above all existing windows, and with
    a transparent background. Then after five seconds, the information displayed will disappear
    and the program will exit.
  </para>
  
  <para>
    In the future, this command will accept some parameters which will render it more
    useful.
  </para>
  
  <sect1>
    <title>Reference</title>
    <para>
      <cmdsynopsis>
        <command>pykosd</command>
      </cmdsynopsis>
      <warning>
        <para>
          <filename>pykosd</filename> doesn't currently accept any command line
          option. This will change in the future.
        </para>  
      </warning>
    </para>
  </sect1>
</chapter>

